Use this README file to introduce your application and point to useful places in the API for learning more.
Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

== API/Model ==
Service:
 - name
 - id
 - group
 * properties

Client: < Provider
   - name
   - id
   - provider_id
   * properties

ServiceClients:
  - serviceId
  - clientId
  - startDate
  - endDate

Backend: < Provider
  - id
  - name
  - provider_id
  * properties

ServiceBackends:
  - service_id
  - backend_id

ServiceRelations: (Used by getPerson, Uses createDocument)
 - service_id
 - related_service_id
 - RelationType, Uses/UsedBy

#(NO, extrapolate this) All combinations should be returnd by backend/regitry. (All directions)


Provider: 
  - id
  - name

Statistics:
  - Type (STI)
  - id
  * metrics (or maybe just use *properties)

Metric:
  - group/scope
  - name
  - value
Ex group: Last day, name: responseTime, value: 100

Documenation
 - Type (STI)
 - Id
 * properties
 * documents

Document:
  - Type(STI) (Asciidoc,Markdown,File,Link)
  - Id
  - DocumentationId
  - Content


